snippet.textDisplay:
🙏🙏🙏🙏🙏
1:39 💛🔥🔥
👇 👇🧡

I think people underrate the poetic levels of this masterpiece. Similarly to Eminem’s ‘Stan’, this piece shows Callux reaching higher levels of desperation for Santa’s approval, like Stan is desperate for Eminem’s approval. There is a dramatic increase going into the second verse of ‘naughty list’, and then do all the short blunt ending of telling the children Santa doesn’t exist marks the breaking point, like Stan driving his pregnant girlfriend over the bridge.
This will be studied in English classes all around the years in the following centuries, I am honoured to exist in the same period of time it was created.
Thank you Callux
